description:
&lt;p&gt;The Staff Counselling Department is seeking to welcome a new Band 6 Staff counsellor unto our team, to help us continue the delivery of responsive and effective psychological support to all our staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must have experience of working within a time-limited model, counselling people from diverse backgrounds and have experience of workplace counselling and workplace issues. They must have a minimum of 2 years post qualification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is Full time , 37.5hrs and will require the applicant to be able to work cross-site at both St. Helier and Epsom Hospitals, providing 1 to 1 counselling, group support and training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;because&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt; of the diverse ethnicity of our staff group we particularly welcome applications from those with a BAME background&#39;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:Therese Lord, Head of Staff Counselling Email: therese.lord@nhs.net 02082962769&lt;/p&gt;
